What is HTML and why is it important ?
HTML is a system that is used for tagging text files to achieve font,color,graphic and some links on web pages. It stands for Hypertext Markup Language. HTML is wtritten
as "<html>" for tagging.

What is CSS and why is it important ?
CSS is used by web pages to help keep information in the proper display format. CSS files can help define font, size, color, spacing, border and location of HTML 
information on a web page, and can also be used to create a continuous look throughout multiple pages of a website. It stands for Cascading Style Sheet.

